Morphology features of CF, CF-Zn and CF-Ni nanoparticles
The morphology of the CF, CF-Zn and CF-Ni nanoparticles were examined by scanning electron microscopy (SEM). Fig. 3 shows the SEM images of the CF, CF-Zn and CF-Ni nanoparticles. These reveal the formation of interconnected spherical-shaped particles with some degree of agglomeration. The morphology of the CF slightly changed after the addition of Zn and Ni ions onto the CF surface. The ionic radius of the Zn and Ni ions influences the morphology of the nanoparticles by varying crystal growth during synthesis. The substitution of Zn and Ni alters the nucleation of the material that slightly changes the morphology of the CF-Ni and CF-Zn. The variation in the morphology and size of the NPs confirmed the successful substitution of Zn and Ni ions. Also, the SEM images of the CF-Zn NPs shows that these possess a hexagonal-shape.
